65 /**
66  * States of the ILCK state machine
67  */
68 typedef enum {
69  /* Init-Sequence */
70  ILCK_STATEMACHINE_UNINITIALIZED, /*!< Uninitialized state */
71  ILCK_STATEMACHINE_INITIALIZED, /*!< statemachine initialized */
72  ILCK_STATEMACHINE_UNDEFINED, /*!< undefined state */
73 } ILCK_STATEMACH_e;
74 
75 /**
76  * Substates of the ILCK state machine
77  */
78 typedef enum {
79  ILCK_ENTRY, /*!< Substate entry state */
80 } ILCK_STATEMACH_SUB_e;
81 
82 /**
83  * State requests for the ILCK statemachine
84  */
85 typedef enum {
86  ILCK_STATE_INITIALIZATION_REQUEST,
87  ILCK_STATE_NO_REQUEST,
88 } ILCK_STATE_REQUEST_e;
89 
90 /**
91  * Possible return values when state requests are made to the ILCK statemachine
92  */
93 typedef enum {
94  ILCK_OK, /*!< ILCK --> ok */
95  ILCK_REQUEST_PENDING, /*!< requested to be executed */
96  ILCK_ALREADY_INITIALIZED, /*!< Initialization of ilck already finished */
97  ILCK_ILLEGAL_REQUEST, /*!< Request can not be executed */
98 } ILCK_RETURN_TYPE_e;
99 
100 /**
101  * This structure contains all the variables relevant for the ILCK state machine.
102  * The user can get the current state of the ILCK state machine with this variable
103  */
104 typedef struct {
105  uint16_t timer; /*!< time in ms before the state machine processes the next state, e.g. in counts of 1ms */
106  ILCK_STATE_REQUEST_e
107  statereq; /*!< current state request made to the state machine */
108  ILCK_STATEMACH_e
109  state; /*!< state of Driver State Machine */
110  ILCK_STATEMACH_SUB_e
111  substate; /*!< current substate of the state machine */
112  ILCK_STATEMACH_e
113  laststate; /*!< previous state of the state machine */
114  ILCK_STATEMACH_SUB_e
115  lastsubstate; /*!< previous substate of the state machine */
116  uint32_t ErrRequestCounter; /*!< counts the number of illegal requests to the LTC state machine */
117  uint8_t triggerentry; /*!< counter for re-entrance protection (function running flag) */
118  uint8_t counter; /*!< general purpose counter */
119 } ILCK_STATE_s;

125 /**
126  * @brief sets the current state request of the state variable ilck_state.
127  *
128  * This function is used to make a state request to the state machine,e.g, start voltage measurement,
129  * read result of voltage measurement, re-initialization
130  * It calls ILCK_CheckStateRequest() to check if the request is valid.
131  * The state request is rejected if is not valid.
132  * The result of the check is returned immediately, so that the requester can act in case
133  * it made a non-valid state request.
134  *
135  * @param statereq state request to set
136  *
137  * @return retVal current state request, taken from ILCK_STATE_REQUEST_e
138  */
139 extern ILCK_RETURN_TYPE_e ILCK_SetStateRequest(ILCK_STATE_REQUEST_e statereq);
140 
141 /**
142  * @brief gets the current state.
143  *
144  * This function is used in the functioning of the ILCK state machine.
145  *
146  * @return current state, taken from ILCK_STATEMACH_e
147  */
148 extern ILCK_STATEMACH_e ILCK_GetState(void);
149 
150 /**
151  * @brief trigger function for the ILCK driver state machine.
152  *
153  * This function contains the sequence of events in the ILCK state machine.
154  * It must be called time-triggered, every 1ms.
155  */
156 extern void ILCK_Trigger(void);
